TY  - JOUR
T1  - Self-Concordance at Work: Toward Understanding the Motivational Effects of Transformational Leaders
AU  - Bono, Joyce E.
AU  - Judge, Timothy A.
Y1  - 2003/10/01
PY  - 2003
DA  - 2003/10/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/30040649
DO  - 10.5465/30040649
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 554
EP  - 571
VL  - 46
IS  - 5
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - We extend existing theories by linking transformational leadership to ?self-concordance? at work. In two studies using diverse samples and methods, leader behaviors were associated with follower tendencies to set self-concordant goals. In general, followers of transformational leaders viewed their work as more important and as more self-congruent. The effects of self-concordant work goals on job attitudes and performance were generally positive; however, the pattern of relationships differed in the field study and the experimental study.
AB  - We extend existing theories by linking transformational leadership to ?self-concordance? at work. In two studies using diverse samples and methods, leader behaviors were associated with follower tendencies to set self-concordant goals. In general, followers of transformational leaders viewed their work as more important and as more self-congruent. The effects of self-concordant work goals on job attitudes and performance were generally positive; however, the pattern of relationships differed in the field study and the experimental study.
